# mekaDoseSigma — agent constraints

Read `mekaDoseSigma/DESIGN.md` for full context. When editing this project, follow these non‑negotiables:

## Platform
- Seeed XIAO ESP32-S3, GC9A01 240×240 round display, CHSC6X touch (I2C 0x2e).
- Jet renderer config lives in `managed_components/jet/src/JetConfig.hpp` only.
- Reference implementation: `basic_engine_test_game/` (display swap, touch rotation, camera patterns).

## Touch-first design (most important)
- **Finger blocks the screen.** Prefer controls that do not require looking at where you tap.
- **Unique input solutions** Using swipes, circle motions, or other unique inputs when possible and appropriate
- Prefer: hold-to-move / release-to-stop, tap edges, or single-thumb zones — not precision taps on actors.
- Keep HUD minimal and in **safe corners** (avoid center 120×120 where finger sits).
- Combat feedback must be readable **peripherally** (color flash, screen edge pulse, large HP bar).

## Scope & performance
- FPS performance is very important, optimization in all areas possible
- Few moving objects on screen; low triangle count; UNLIT where possible.
- One enemy or small squad max until FPS is proven.
- No feature without a playable touch test on device.

## Code layout (target)
- `main/game/` — game logic only; no display driver code in game files.
- Shared touch zones in one header; one place for input semantics.
- Constants for hit radii, spawn distance, and UI zones — no magic numbers scattered.

## When unsure
- Choose the option that is **easier to play on a 240px circle**, not the option that looks coolest in a screenshot.
